#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:3
msgid "Settings"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:5
msgid ""
"There are some advanced settings, which you can alter in "
":menuselection:`Interfaces --> Settings`, most of the time you should "
"leave these settings default, but advanced scenarios may require specific"
" settings."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:8
msgid ""
"The settings on this page will be applied after reboot or a "
"reconfiguration of each interface."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:12
msgid "Hardware CRC"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:13
msgid ""
"Disable hardware checksum offloading, which is checked by default, "
"controls if user-configurable checksum offloading might be handled by the"
" network card. Not all technologies support this (IPS for example) and "
"some drivers have issues when enabled. We generally advise to keep this "
"disabled, the performance gain is debatable as well."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:17
msgid ""
"(the :code:`ifconfig` settings in the OS related to this setting are "
":code:`txcsum` , :code:`rxcsum` , :code:`txcsum6` , :code:`rxcsum6`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:22
msgid "Hardware TSO"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:23
msgid ""
"Disable hardware TCP segmentation offload, also checked by default, "
"prevents the system to offload packet segmentation to the network card. "
"This option is incompatible with IPS in OPNsense and is broken in some "
"network cards."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:26
msgid ""
"(the :code:`ifconfig` settings in the OS related to this setting are "
":code:`tso` ,  :code:`tso4` , :code:`tso6`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:30
msgid "Hardware LRO"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:31
msgid ""
"Disable hardware large receive offload, which is checked by default, "
"prevents the network card from aggregating incoming packets into a larger"
" buffer before passing it further on the network stack (in order to "
"decrease the number of packets to process)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:34
msgid ""
"For routing traffic its usually advisable to disable options which queue "
"traffic in the network card to prevent additional latency."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:36
msgid ""
"Enabling LRO might degrade routing performance or for some drivers is "
"incompatible with packet-forwarding at all."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:38
msgid ""
"(the :code:`ifconfig` setting in the OS related to this setting is "
":code:`lro`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:43
msgid "VLAN Hardware Filtering"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:45
msgid ""
"Set usage of VLAN hardware filtering. This hardware acceleration may be "
"broken in some device drivers, our advice is to keep this setting on "
"\"Disable VLAN Hardware Filtering\", which is the default as of 20.7. In "
"some cases (pre 20.7) we have seen random disconnects when the driver is "
"forced into a mode it was not set at by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:51
msgid ""
"(the :code:`ifconfig` settings in the OS related to this setting are "
":code:`vlanhwtag`, :code:`vlanhwcsum` ,  :code:`vlanhwfilter` , "
":code:`vlanhwtso`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:55
msgid "ARP Handling"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:56
msgid ""
"By default the kernel logs movement of ip addresses from one hardware "
"address to another and when an arp request is received on the wrong "
"interface. When checking this option, it will stop doing so, which is "
"practical if multiple interfaces reside on the same broadcast domain."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:59
msgid ""
"(for a more detailed description, see :code:`man arp` and search "
":code:`log_arp_wrong_iface` and  :code:`log_arp_movements`)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:63
msgid "DHCP Unique Identifier"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:64
msgid ""
"This option can be used to enter an explicit DUID for use by IPv6 DHCP "
"clients, the different types are detailed in `section 11 of rfc8415 "
"<https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc8415#section-11>`__"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/manual/interfaces_settings.rst:67
msgid ""
"When not set, the dhcp v6 client (:code:`dhcp6c`) will assign one "
"automatically."
msgstr ""

